Lütken, 1892
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="191" pageNumber="192" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="191.[151,1437,150,1653]" pageId="191" pageNumber="192">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[603,856,1302,1328]" pageId="191" pageNumber="192">Luminous Swallower</emphasis>
. To 
<quantity box="[907,997,1303,1329]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.72" pageId="191" pageNumber="192" unit="cm" value="17.2">17.2 cm</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[1013,1080,1302,1330]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.905" pageId="191" pageNumber="192" unit="in" value="7.5">7.5 in</quantity>
) SL (Mecklenburg 
<emphasis box="[1300,1357,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="191" pageNumber="192">et al.</emphasis>
2002). Circumglobal; western Pacific Ocean north to 
<collectingCountry box="[702,766,1339,1365]" name="Japan" pageId="191" pageNumber="192">Japan</collectingCountry>
(Okamura in 
<bibRefCitation author="Okamura" box="[913,1136,1338,1365]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Okamura" pageId="191" pageNumber="192" refId="ref306433" refString="Okamura, O., Machida, Y., Yamakawa, T., Matsuura, K. &amp; Yatou, T. (Eds.). (1985) Fishes of the Okinawa Trough and the Adjacent waters. Volume 2. The Intensive Research of Unexploited Fishery Resources on Continental Slopes. Japan Fisheries Conservation Association, Tokyo." type="book" year="1985">
Okamura 
<emphasis box="[1022,1075,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="191" pageNumber="192">et al.</emphasis>
1985
</bibRefCitation>
) and southern Kuril Islands (
<bibRefCitation author="Parin" box="[205,394,1374,1401]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Parin" pageId="191" pageNumber="192" pagination="193 - 204" refId="ref309690" refString="Parin, N. V., Fedorov, V. V., Borodulina, O. D. &amp; Bekker, V. E. (1995) New records of mesopelagic and epipelagic fishes in Pacific waters off the southern Kuril Islands. Journal of Ichthyology, 35, 193 - 204." type="journal article" year="1995">
Parin 
<emphasis box="[272,328,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="191" pageNumber="192">et al.</emphasis>
1995
</bibRefCitation>
); western Bering Sea off northeastern Kamchatka and vicinity of Commander Islands (
<bibRefCitation author="Sheiko and Fedorov" firstAuthor="Sheiko" pageId="191" pageNumber="192" pagination="7 - 69" refId="ref321798" refString="Sheiko, B. A. &amp; Fedorov, V. V. (2000) Chapter 1. Class Cephalaspidomorphi - Lampreys. Class Chondrichthyes - Cartilaginous fishes. Class Holocephali - Chimaeras. Class Osteichthyes - Bony fishes. In: Catalog of Vertebrates of Kamchatka and Adjacent Waters. Kamchatsky Pechatny Dvor, Petropavlovsk-Kamchatsky, Russia, pp. 7 - 69 [In Russian.]" type="book chapter" year="2000">Sheiko and Fedorov 2000</bibRefCitation>
); 
<specimenCount box="[426,579,1411,1437]" pageId="191" pageNumber="192" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
taken in “NMFS Area 670, 
<geoCoordinate box="[893,989,1411,1437]" degrees="47" direction="north" minutes="30" orientation="latitude" pageId="191" pageNumber="192" precision="925" value="47.5">47°30’N</geoCoordinate>
to 
<geoCoordinate box="[1025,1124,1410,1437]" degrees="50" direction="north" minutes="30" orientation="latitude" pageId="191" pageNumber="192" precision="925" value="50.5">50°30’N</geoCoordinate>
” (Personal communication: University of Washington, Burke Museum of Natural History and Culture Fish Collection, Seattle, Washington, 
<accessionNumber box="[198,341,1482,1509]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/UW153507" pageId="191" pageNumber="192">UW 153507</accessionNumber>
); probably inhabits deep waters north and south of the Aleutian Islands and in the Gulf of Alaska (Mecklenburg 
<emphasis box="[364,422,1519,1545]" italics="true" pageId="191" pageNumber="192">et al.</emphasis>
2002). Mesopelagic and bathypelagic; depth: 
<quantity box="[949,1098,1519,1545]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="2.1" metricValueMin="0.2" pageId="191" pageNumber="192" unit="m" value="1150.0" valueMax="2100.0" valueMin="200.0">200–2,100 m</quantity>
(
<quantity box="[1114,1262,1518,1546]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1500103999999998" metricValueMax="2.100072" metricValueMin="0.1999488" pageId="191" pageNumber="192" unit="ft" value="3773.0" valueMax="6890.0" valueMin="656.0">656–6,890 ft</quantity>
) (Mecklenburg 
<emphasis box="[198,255,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="191" pageNumber="192">et al.</emphasis>
2002). A taxon with confused taxonomy. The western Pacific form 
<taxonomicName authority="Tanaka, 1908" authorityName="Tanaka" authorityYear="1908" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="191" pageNumber="192" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="scriptus" subSpecies="sagamianus">
<emphasis box="[1020,1436,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="191" pageNumber="192">Pseudoscopelus scriptus sagamianus</emphasis>
Tanaka, 1908
</taxonomicName>
, has been treated as a separate species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tanaka" authorityYear="1908" box="[792,953,1591,1616]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="191" pageNumber="192" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sagamianus">
<emphasis box="[792,953,1591,1616]" italics="true" pageId="191" pageNumber="192">P. sagamianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Melo" box="[968,1157,1591,1617]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Melo" pageId="191" pageNumber="192" pagination="33 - 46" refId="ref301697" refString="Melo, M. R. S., Walker Jr, H. J. &amp; Klepadlo, C. (2007) Two new species of Pseudoscopelus (Teleostei: Chiasmodontidae), with a new diagnosis for the genus. Zootaxa, 1605, 33 - 46. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1605.1.2" type="journal article" year="2007">
Melo 
<emphasis box="[1035,1092,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="191" pageNumber="192">et al.</emphasis>
2007
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Prokofiev" box="[1168,1346,1591,1617]" firstAuthor="Prokofiev" pageId="191" pageNumber="192" pagination="10 - 22" refId="ref314576" refString="Prokofiev, A. M. (2009) Pseudoscopelus sagamianus Tanaka 1908 (Chiasmodontidae): designation of the neotype, morphological characteristics of the North Pacific population, and species variation within its whole area. Journal of Ichthyology, 49, 10 - 22. https: // doi. org / 10.1134 / s 0032945209010020" type="journal article" year="2009">Prokofiev 2009</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Fricke" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Fricke" pageId="191" pageNumber="192" refId="ref280407" refString="Fricke, R., Eschmeyer, W. N. &amp; van der Laan, R. (Eds). 2020. Eschmeyer's Catalog of Fishes: Genera, Species, Reference. Available from: http: // researcharchive. calacademy. org / research / ichthyology / catalog / fishcatmain. asp (accessed 17 April 2021)." type="url" year="2020">
Fricke 
<emphasis box="[198,254,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="191" pageNumber="192">et al.</emphasis>
(2020)
</bibRefCitation>
do not recognize the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[650,829,1627,1653]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Chiasmodontidae" genus="Pseudoscopelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="191" pageNumber="192" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[650,829,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="191" pageNumber="192">Pseudoscopelus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from within our range.
</paragraph>
